33// Helper class for extracting VP9 colorspace.
34ColorSpace ExtractVP9ColorSpace(vpx_color_space_t space_t,
35 vpx_color_range_t range_t,
36 unsigned int bit_depth) {
37 ColorSpace::PrimaryID primaries = ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kUnspecified;
38 ColorSpace::TransferID transfer = ColorSpace::TransferID::kUnspecified;
39 ColorSpace::MatrixID matrix = ColorSpace::MatrixID::kUnspecified;
40 switch (space_t) {
41 case VPX_CS_BT_601:
42 case VPX_CS_SMPTE_170:
43 primaries = ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kSMPTE170M;
44 transfer = ColorSpace::TransferID::kSMPTE170M;
45 matrix = ColorSpace::MatrixID::kSMPTE170M;
46 break;
47 case VPX_CS_SMPTE_240:
48 primaries = ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kSMPTE240M;
49 transfer = ColorSpace::TransferID::kSMPTE240M;
50 matrix = ColorSpace::MatrixID::kSMPTE240M;
51 break;
52 case VPX_CS_BT_709:
53 primaries = ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kBT709;
54 transfer = ColorSpace::TransferID::kBT709;
55 matrix = ColorSpace::MatrixID::kBT709;
56 break;
57 case VPX_CS_BT_2020:
58 primaries = ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kBT2020;
59 switch (bit_depth) {
60 case 8:
61 transfer = ColorSpace::TransferID::kBT709;
62 break;
63 case 10:
64 transfer = ColorSpace::TransferID::kBT2020_10;
65 break;
66 default:
67 RTC_NOTREACHED();
68 break;
69 }
70 matrix = ColorSpace::MatrixID::kBT2020_NCL;
71 break;
72 case VPX_CS_SRGB:
73 primaries = ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kBT709;
74 transfer = ColorSpace::TransferID::kIEC61966_2_1;
75 matrix = ColorSpace::MatrixID::kBT709;
76 break;
77 default:
78 break;
79 }
80
81 ColorSpace::RangeID range = ColorSpace::RangeID::kInvalid;
82 switch (range_t) {
83 case VPX_CR_STUDIO_RANGE:
84 range = ColorSpace::RangeID::kLimited;
85 break;
86 case VPX_CR_FULL_RANGE:
87 range = ColorSpace::RangeID::kFull;
88 break;
89 default:
90 break;
91 }
92 return ColorSpace(primaries, transfer, matrix, range);
93}
94
95} // namespace

97LibvpxVp9Decoder::LibvpxVp9Decoder()
98 : LibvpxVp9Decoder(FieldTrialBasedConfig()) {}
99LibvpxVp9Decoder::LibvpxVp9Decoder(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials)
100 : decode_complete_callback_(nullptr),
101 inited_(false),
102 decoder_(nullptr),
103 key_frame_required_(true),
104 preferred_output_format_(
105 absl::StartsWith(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-NV12Decode"), "Enabled")
106 ? VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNV12
107 : VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kI420) {}
108
109LibvpxVp9Decoder::~LibvpxVp9Decoder() {
110 inited_ = true; // in order to do the actual release
111 Release();
112 int num_buffers_in_use = libvpx_buffer_pool_.GetNumBuffersInUse();
113 if (num_buffers_in_use > 0) {
114 // The frame buffers are reference counted and frames are exposed after
115 // decoding. There may be valid usage cases where previous frames are still
116 // referenced after ~LibvpxVp9Decoder that is not a leak.
117 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << num_buffers_in_use
118 << " Vp9FrameBuffers are still "
119 "referenced during ~LibvpxVp9Decoder.";
120 }
121}
122
123int LibvpxVp9Decoder::InitDecode(const VideoCodec* inst, int number_of_cores) {
124 int ret_val = Release();
125 if (ret_val < 0) {
126 return ret_val;
127 }
128
129 if (decoder_ == nullptr) {
130 decoder_ = new vpx_codec_ctx_t;
131 }
132 vpx_codec_dec_cfg_t cfg;
133 memset(&cfg, 0, sizeof(cfg));
134
135#ifdef FUZZING_BUILD_MODE_UNSAFE_FOR_PRODUCTION
136 // We focus on webrtc fuzzing here, not libvpx itself. Use single thread for
137 // fuzzing, because:
138 // - libvpx's VP9 single thread decoder is more fuzzer friendly. It detects
139 // errors earlier than the multi-threads version.
140 // - Make peak CPU usage under control (not depending on input)
141 cfg.threads = 1;
142#else
143 if (!inst) {
144 // No config provided - don't know resolution to decode yet.
145 // Set thread count to one in the meantime.
146 cfg.threads = 1;
147 } else {
148 // We want to use multithreading when decoding high resolution videos. But
149 // not too many in order to avoid overhead when many stream are decoded
150 // concurrently.
151 // Set 2 thread as target for 1280x720 pixel count, and then scale up
152 // linearly from there - but cap at physical core count.
153 // For common resolutions this results in:
154 // 1 for 360p
155 // 2 for 720p
156 // 4 for 1080p
157 // 8 for 1440p
158 // 18 for 4K
159 int num_threads =
160 std::max(1, 2 * (inst->width * inst->height) / (1280 * 720));
161 cfg.threads = std::min(number_of_cores, num_threads);
162 current_codec_ = *inst;
163 }
164#endif
165
166 num_cores_ = number_of_cores;
167
168 vpx_codec_flags_t flags = 0;
169 if (vpx_codec_dec_init(decoder_, vpx_codec_vp9_dx(), &cfg, flags)) {
170 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_MEMORY;
171 }
172
173 if (!libvpx_buffer_pool_.InitializeVpxUsePool(decoder_)) {
174 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_MEMORY;
175 }
176
177 inited_ = true;
178 // Always start with a complete key frame.
179 key_frame_required_ = true;
180 if (inst && inst->buffer_pool_size) {
181 if (!libvpx_buffer_pool_.Resize(*inst->buffer_pool_size) ||
182 !output_buffer_pool_.Resize(*inst->buffer_pool_size)) {
183 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
184 }
185 }
186
187 vpx_codec_err_t status =
188 vpx_codec_control(decoder_, VP9D_SET_LOOP_FILTER_OPT, 1);
189 if (status != VPX_CODEC_OK) {
190 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to enable VP9D_SET_LOOP_FILTER_OPT. "
191 << vpx_codec_error(decoder_);
192 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
193 }
194
195 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
196}
197
198int LibvpxVp9Decoder::Decode(const EncodedImage& input_image,
199 bool missing_frames,
200 int64_t /*render_time_ms*/) {
201 if (!inited_) {
202 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
203 }
204 if (decode_complete_callback_ == nullptr) {
205 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
206 }
207
208 if (input_image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
209 absl::optional<vp9::FrameInfo> frame_info =
210 vp9::ParseIntraFrameInfo(input_image.data(), input_image.size());
211 if (frame_info) {
212 if (frame_info->frame_width != current_codec_.width ||
213 frame_info->frame_height != current_codec_.height) {
214 // Resolution has changed, tear down and re-init a new decoder in
215 // order to get correct sizing.
216 Release();
217 current_codec_.width = frame_info->frame_width;
218 current_codec_.height = frame_info->frame_height;
219 int reinit_status = InitDecode(&current_codec_, num_cores_);
220 if (reinit_status != WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
221 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to re-init decoder.";
222 return reinit_status;
223 }
224 }
225 } else {
226 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to parse VP9 header from key-frame.";
227 }
228 }
229
230 // Always start with a complete key frame.
231 if (key_frame_required_) {
232 if (input_image._frameType != VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey)
233 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
234 key_frame_required_ = false;
235 }
236 vpx_codec_iter_t iter = nullptr;
237 vpx_image_t* img;
238 const uint8_t* buffer = input_image.data();
239 if (input_image.size() == 0) {
240 buffer = nullptr; // Triggers full frame concealment.
241 }
242 // During decode libvpx may get and release buffers from
243 // |libvpx_buffer_pool_|. In practice libvpx keeps a few (~3-4) buffers alive
244 // at a time.
245 if (vpx_codec_decode(decoder_, buffer,
246 static_cast<unsigned int>(input_image.size()), 0,
247 VPX_DL_REALTIME)) {
248 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
249 }
250 // |img->fb_priv| contains the image data, a reference counted Vp9FrameBuffer.
251 // It may be released by libvpx during future vpx_codec_decode or
252 // vpx_codec_destroy calls.
253 img = vpx_codec_get_frame(decoder_, &iter);
254 int qp;
255 vpx_codec_err_t vpx_ret =
256 vpx_codec_control(decoder_, VPXD_GET_LAST_QUANTIZER, &qp);
257 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(vpx_ret, VPX_CODEC_OK);
258 int ret =
259 ReturnFrame(img, input_image.Timestamp(), qp, input_image.ColorSpace());
260 if (ret != 0) {
261 return ret;
262 }
263 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
264}
265
266int LibvpxVp9Decoder::ReturnFrame(
267 const vpx_image_t* img,
268 uint32_t timestamp,
269 int qp,
270 const webrtc::ColorSpace* explicit_color_space) {
271 if (img == nullptr) {
272 // Decoder OK and nullptr image => No show frame.
273 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_NO_OUTPUT;
274 }
275
276 // This buffer contains all of |img|'s image data, a reference counted
277 // Vp9FrameBuffer. (libvpx is done with the buffers after a few
278 // vpx_codec_decode calls or vpx_codec_destroy).
279 rtc::scoped_refptr<Vp9FrameBufferPool::Vp9FrameBuffer> img_buffer =
280 static_cast<Vp9FrameBufferPool::Vp9FrameBuffer*>(img->fb_priv);
281
282 // The buffer can be used directly by the VideoFrame (without copy) by
283 // using a Wrapped*Buffer.
284 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoFrameBuffer> img_wrapped_buffer;
285 switch (img->bit_depth) {
286 case 8:
287 if (img->fmt == VPX_IMG_FMT_I420) {
288 if (preferred_output_format_ == VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNV12) {
289 rtc::scoped_refptr<NV12Buffer> nv12_buffer =
290 output_buffer_pool_.CreateNV12Buffer(img->d_w, img->d_h);
291 if (!nv12_buffer.get()) {
292 // Buffer pool is full.
293 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_NO_OUTPUT;
294 }
295 img_wrapped_buffer = nv12_buffer;
296 libyuv::I420ToNV12(img->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y], img->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y],
297 img->planes[VPX_PLANE_U], img->stride[VPX_PLANE_U],
298 img->planes[VPX_PLANE_V], img->stride[VPX_PLANE_V],
299 nv12_buffer->MutableDataY(),
300 nv12_buffer->StrideY(),
301 nv12_buffer->MutableDataUV(),
302 nv12_buffer->StrideUV(), img->d_w, img->d_h);
303 // No holding onto img_buffer as it's no longer needed and can be
304 // reused.
305 } else {
306 img_wrapped_buffer = WrapI420Buffer(
307 img->d_w, img->d_h, img->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y],
308 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y], img->planes[VPX_PLANE_U],
309 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_U], img->planes[VPX_PLANE_V],
310 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_V],
311 // WrappedI420Buffer's mechanism for allowing the release of its
312 // frame buffer is through a callback function. This is where we
313 // should release |img_buffer|.
314 [img_buffer] {});
315 }
316 } else if (img->fmt == VPX_IMG_FMT_I444) {
317 img_wrapped_buffer = WrapI444Buffer(
318 img->d_w, img->d_h, img->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y],
319 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y], img->planes[VPX_PLANE_U],
320 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_U], img->planes[VPX_PLANE_V],
321 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_V],
322 // WrappedI444Buffer's mechanism for allowing the release of its
323 // frame buffer is through a callback function. This is where we
324 // should release |img_buffer|.
325 [img_buffer] {});
326 } else {
327 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
328 << "Unsupported pixel format produced by the decoder: "
329 << static_cast<int>(img->fmt);
330 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_NO_OUTPUT;
331 }
332 break;
333 case 10:
334 img_wrapped_buffer = WrapI010Buffer(
335 img->d_w, img->d_h,
336 reinterpret_cast<const uint16_t*>(img->planes[VPX_PLANE_Y]),
337 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_Y] / 2,
338 reinterpret_cast<const uint16_t*>(img->planes[VPX_PLANE_U]),
339 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_U] / 2,
340 reinterpret_cast<const uint16_t*>(img->planes[VPX_PLANE_V]),
341 img->stride[VPX_PLANE_V] / 2, [img_buffer] {});
342 break;
343 default:
344 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unsupported bit depth produced by the decoder: "
345 << img->bit_depth;
346 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_NO_OUTPUT;
347 }
348
349 auto builder = VideoFrame::Builder()
350 .set_video_frame_buffer(img_wrapped_buffer)
351 .set_timestamp_rtp(timestamp);
352 if (explicit_color_space) {
353 builder.set_color_space(*explicit_color_space);
354 } else {
355 builder.set_color_space(
356 ExtractVP9ColorSpace(img->cs, img->range, img->bit_depth));
357 }
358 VideoFrame decoded_image = builder.build();
359
360 decode_complete_callback_->Decoded(decoded_image, absl::nullopt, qp);
361 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
362}
363
364int LibvpxVp9Decoder::RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(
365 DecodedImageCallback* callback) {
366 decode_complete_callback_ = callback;
367 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
368}
369
370int LibvpxVp9Decoder::Release() {
371 int ret_val = WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
372
373 if (decoder_ != nullptr) {
374 if (inited_) {
375 // When a codec is destroyed libvpx will release any buffers of
376 // |libvpx_buffer_pool_| it is currently using.
377 if (vpx_codec_destroy(decoder_)) {
378 ret_val = WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_MEMORY;
379 }
380 }
381 delete decoder_;
382 decoder_ = nullptr;
383 }
384 // Releases buffers from the pool. Any buffers not in use are deleted. Buffers
385 // still referenced externally are deleted once fully released, not returning
386 // to the pool.
387 libvpx_buffer_pool_.ClearPool();
388 output_buffer_pool_.Release();
389 inited_ = false;
390 return ret_val;
391}

393VideoDecoder::DecoderInfo LibvpxVp9Decoder::GetDecoderInfo() const {
394 DecoderInfo info;
395 info.implementation_name = "libvpx";
396 info.is_hardware_accelerated = false;
397 return info;
398}

400const char* LibvpxVp9Decoder::ImplementationName() const {
401 return "libvpx";
402}
